# Systematic Review Automation Tool

## Project Identity
- **Purpose:** Automate systematic literature reviews to produce IEEE-submission-ready manuscripts
- **Stack:** Python 3.11+, PydanticAI Graph, SQLite, Google Gemini (3-tier: lite/flash/pro per agent), statsmodels, matplotlib
- **Frontend:** React 19, Vite 7, TypeScript, Tailwind 4, Recharts, cmdk, Radix UI
- **Package manager:** uv (Python), pnpm (frontend)
- **Architecture:** Typed state, SQLite persistence, 3-tier LLM model selection, FastAPI web server
- **LLM config:** Model names per agent live in `config/settings.yaml` under `agents:`. Do NOT hardcode model strings in code -- always read from config. The tier mapping (lite = highest throughput, flash = balanced, pro = highest quality) is the stable abstraction; the exact model name strings will change as Google releases new versions.

## Key Directories -- Backend
- `src/main.py` -- CLI entry point (uv run python -m src.main)
- `src/config/` -- config loader (loader.py); reads review.yaml + settings.yaml into typed models
- `src/models/` -- Pydantic data contracts (enums, config, papers, screening, extraction, quality, writing, workflow, diagrams, claims, additional)
- `src/db/` -- SQLite schema (schema.sql), connection manager (database.py), typed repositories (repositories.py), workflow registry (workflow_registry.py)
- `src/orchestration/` -- quality gates (gates.py), workflow graph (workflow.py), context (context.py), resume (resume.py), state (state.py), embedding_node.py, knowledge_graph_node.py; StartNode writes config_snapshot.yaml (with workflow_id in header) to the run dir and pre-registers ALL artifact paths (including manuscript_tex, references_bib); FinalizeNode generates doc_manuscript.tex and references.bib as first-class run artifacts (no POST /export needed), then writes total_cost to run_summary.json (queried from cost_records); ExtractionQualityNode saves PDF/TXT to papers/ and updates data_papers_manifest.json
- `src/search/` -- base connector protocol (base.py), OpenAlex (no is_core filter; broad search with type:article + source:journal + is_retracted:false quality gates), PubMed, arXiv, IEEE Xplore, Semantic Scholar, Crossref, Perplexity auxiliary, Scopus, Web of Science (web_of_science.py; Clarivate WoS Starter API, X-ApiKey auth, TS= prefix, 300 req/day free; raises RuntimeError on quota exhaustion instead of silent 0-result success), Embase (embase.py; Elsevier institutional API, EMBASE_API_KEY required) + dedup + strategy (build_boolean_query uses keywords only, not PICO descriptions; clinicaltrials_gov case added; SearchStrategyCoordinator.low_recall_threshold warns when any connector returns < settings.search.low_recall_warning_threshold records) + citation_chasing (Semantic Scholar/OpenAlex forward search) + clinicaltrials (ClinicalTrials.gov grey literature) + csv_import (master list CSV pipeline) + pdf_retrieval.py (PDFRetrievalResult now includes pdf_bytes and source fields; retrieve() works on paper.url as well as paper.doi)
- `src/screening/` -- Dual-reviewer screener (dual_screener.py), batch_ranker.py (batch LLM pre-ranker between BM25 and dual-reviewer; `batch_screener` agent key in settings.yaml; papers below `batch_screen_threshold` (0.35) are auto-excluded as `batch_screened_low`; `reviewer_batch_size` (default 10 in settings.yaml) sends N papers per dual-reviewer LLM call -- this is a pure API efficiency change, not a methodological stage; 0 = per-paper legacy mode), prompts, reliability (Cohen's kappa), criteria_refinement, keyword_filter, gemini_client.py (screening-specific LLM client); configurable `insufficient_content_min_words` (currently 0 in settings.yaml; lowered progressively from 12->5->0; at 0, records with empty abstracts reach the LLM dual-screener which can exclude on title alone); fulltext no-PDF exclusion path fires `on_screening_decision` with reason=`fulltext_no_pdf_heuristic` (visible in Activity log)
- `src/extraction/` -- agentic study classifier (study_classifier.py) + structured extraction (extractor.py) + table_extraction
- `src/quality/` -- RoB 2 (rob2.py), ROBINS-I (robins_i.py), CASP (casp.py), MMAT (mmat.py), GRADE (grade.py), study router (study_router.py); all four tool types now persist to structured DB rows: `rob_assessments`, `casp_assessments`, `mmat_assessments` (added); GRADE aggregates per unique outcome name across all papers after the per-paper loop (no longer per-paper overwrite)
- `src/synthesis/` -- Meta-analysis (meta_analysis.py), effect sizes, narrative (LLM direction classification), sensitivity analysis (leave-one-out + subgroup), contradiction_detector, feasibility assessment (feasibility.py)
- `src/writing/` -- Section writer (section_writer.py), prompts/, humanizer, citation_grounding.py (repair_hallucinated_citekeys() fuzzy-matches unknown citekeys against citations table by author_token+year; uses re.sub to replace ALL occurrences of each bad key; falls back to [CITATION_NEEDED] only when no match found), contradiction_resolver, context_builder.py (WritingGroundingData + format_grounding_block; fields include: search_eligibility_window, fulltext_retrieved_count/fulltext_total_count, author_name, records_after_deduplication (pre-computed; injected verbatim so LLM never performs this subtraction), records_excluded_screening (pre-computed; same rationale), rob_summary (structured RoB2/ROBINS-I assessment summary injected into grounding block), grade_summary (GRADE outcome certainty table injected into grounding block); CITATION CATALOG block injected listing every exact citekey with title snippet -- writing LLM must use ONLY these citekeys), orchestration.py (register_methodology_citations, _METHODOLOGY_REFS for PRISMA/GRADE/RoB citekeys, register_background_sr_citations with ASCII surname normalization via unicodedata, prepare_writing_context); NOTE: naturalness_scorer.py was removed (dead code -- score always 0.8, never called); style_extractor fallback path removed (always returned empty patterns)
- `src/rag/` -- RAG pipeline: chunker, embedder (PydanticAI Embedder), hybrid BM25+dense retriever (retriever.py, RRF fusion), hyde.py (HyDE hypothetical doc generation), reranker.py (LLM listwise reranker) -- used by citation grounding and WritingNode
- `src/knowledge_graph/` -- builder, community (Louvain), gap_detector
- `src/citation/` -- Citation ledger (ledger.py) -- tracks claim->evidence->citation lineage
- `src/prisma/` -- PRISMA 2020 flow diagram (diagram.py)
- `src/protocol/` -- PROSPERO-format protocol generator (generator.py)
- `src/visualization/` -- Forest plot, funnel plot, RoB figure, timeline, geographic, concept_diagrams (SVG export), evidence_network.py (force-directed knowledge graph)
- `src/export/` -- IEEE LaTeX (ieee_latex.py; emits `\author{}` when `author_name` is set in ReviewConfig), IEEE compliance validator (ieee_validator.py), Word DOCX exporter (docx_exporter.py, pypandoc-binary + python-docx post-processing), submission packager (bundles fig_funnel_plot.png + fig_rob2_traffic_light.png in addition to other figures), PRISMA checklist validator (prisma_checklist.py), BibTeX builder (bibtex_builder.py), markdown reference formatter (markdown_refs.py; includes _normalize_doi() for https://doi.org/ standardization, _capitalize_name_part() for author name fixes, PICOS Study Design row)
- `src/llm/` -- LLM client stack: base_client.py, pydantic_client.py (PydanticAI agent factory; _run_with_retry: 5 retries, 2-90s exponential backoff with jitter; Retry-After header parsing -- when a 429 carries Retry-After, the wait is max(exponential_delay, retry_after)), gemini_client.py, provider.py, rate_limiter.py (sliding-window RPM limiter per tier: pro/flash/flash-lite; on_waiting fires immediately on first wait, then every 30s; reserve_call_slot() now called before every pro/flash LLM call in extractor.py, section_writer.py/orchestration.py, humanizer, rob2, robins_i, casp, mmat), model_fallback.py (get_fallback_model(tier) -- reads settings.yaml first, falls back to _TIER_LAST_RESORT constants; use this instead of hardcoding model strings anywhere in src/); all calls logged with model/tokens/cost/latency to cost_records table
- `src/web/` -- FastAPI backend (app.py): run lifecycle, SSE streaming, history, DB explorer, log streaming; config_generator.py: LLM-based review config generation from a research question
- `src/utils/` -- logging_paths.py (PM2 log path detection), ssl_context.py, structured_log.py
- `scripts/` -- finalize_manuscript.py (IMRaD heading injection + post-run fixup), migrate_to_runs.py, re_extract.py (targeted re-extraction for low-quality studies), benchmark.py (gold-standard corpus comparison: screening recall, extraction accuracy, RoB kappa), build_benchmark.py (builds/updates gold-standard benchmark from reference/ PDFs using PDF vision LLM; optionally fetches additional published SRs via --fetch-web), show_run_info.py (print run metadata by workflow ID without opening the browser)
- `run_index/` -- (not present on disk; documented feature not yet implemented) intended to hold one YAML stub per workflow for VS Code search visibility.
- `config/` -- review.yaml (per-review topic config) + settings.yaml (agent model tiers + thresholds -- single source of truth for ALL LLM model names; 17 agent keys: screening_reviewer_a/b, screening_adjudicator, batch_screener, search, extraction, quality_assessment, study_type_detection, writing, abstract_generation, humanizer, contradiction_resolver, criteria_refinement, table_extraction, config_generation, concept_diagrams, narrative; plus rag.embed_model/hyde_model/reranker_model and extraction.pdf_vision_model)

