## Key Tables
- `workflows` (per-run runtime.db) -- topic, config_hash, status
- `workflows_registry` (central `{run_root}/workflows_registry.db`) -- workflow_id, topic, config_hash, db_path, status, heartbeat_at
- `event_log` (per-run runtime.db) -- SSE event replay buffer; fields: workflow_id, event_type, payload, ts
- `cost_records` (per-run runtime.db) -- **single source of truth for all LLM call costs**; fields: model, phase, tokens_in, tokens_out, cost_usd, latency_ms; one row per LLM call written atomically by `src/llm/`; `/api/db/{run_id}/costs` and `_fetch_run_stats()` both read `SUM(cost_usd)` from here; `run_summary.json` total_cost is also derived from this table at finalize

## Web API
- FastAPI backend on port 8001 (dev) / 8000 (prod), Vite dev server on port 5173
- Run lifecycle: POST /api/run, GET /api/stream/{run_id}, POST /api/cancel/{run_id}, GET /api/runs
- Results: GET /api/results/{run_id}, GET /api/run/{run_id}/artifacts, POST /api/run/{run_id}/export, GET /api/run/{run_id}/submission.zip, GET /api/run/{run_id}/manuscript.docx
- References tab: GET /api/run/{run_id}/papers-reference (included papers + file availability), GET /api/run/{run_id}/papers/{paper_id}/file (stream PDF or TXT), POST /api/run/{run_id}/fetch-pdfs (retroactive full-text fetch for completed runs, returns {attempted, succeeded, failed})
- History: GET /api/history, GET /api/history/{workflow_id}/config, POST /api/history/resume, POST /api/history/attach, DELETE /api/history/{workflow_id} (delete run + registry entry)
- DB explorer: GET /api/db/{run_id}/papers, /papers-all (includes doi + url for clickable links), /papers-facets, /papers-suggest, /screening, /costs
- Event replay: GET /api/run/{run_id}/events, GET /api/workflow/{workflow_id}/events
- Log streaming: GET /api/logs/stream?run_id={run_id} (SSE, per-run PM2 log tail)
- Config: GET /api/config/review, GET /api/health, POST /api/config/generate (AI config generation from research question), GET /api/config/env-keys (returns API keys already set in server .env for UI pre-fill)
- Human-in-the-loop: GET /api/run/{run_id}/screening-summary, POST /api/run/{run_id}/approve-screening
- Living review: POST /api/run/{run_id}/living-refresh (creates incremental re-run from last_search_date)
- PRISMA compliance: GET /api/run/{run_id}/prisma-checklist
- Stale detection: heartbeat updated every 60s; runs with no heartbeat for 5+ min become "stale"
- Concurrent resume guard: if same workflow_id already active, returns existing run_id (no duplicate task)

## Critical Constraints
- **Use `rich`** for CLI output (progress bars, tables, status)
- **Verify APIs** before embedding: use @Ref or Exa to check current docs for statsmodels, pydantic_graph, aiosqlite, etc. Do not embed outdated code patterns.
- **NO untyped dictionaries** at phase boundaries -- only Pydantic models
- **NO LLM-computed statistics** -- meta-analysis uses scipy/statsmodels only
- **ALL I/O is async** (aiosqlite, aiohttp)
- **ALL LLM calls logged** with model, tokens, cost, latency to cost_records table
- **Citation lineage enforced** -- every claim must trace to evidence to citation
- **NEVER hardcode model name strings** in source code -- always read from `config/settings.yaml` via the config loader. Model names change with Google releases; `settings.yaml` is the single source of truth.
- See `config/review.yaml` for per-review topic config, `config/settings.yaml` for agent model tiers + thresholds

## Strict Commit Safety
- NEVER stage or commit `.env`, `runs/**`, or topic/run-specific generated artifacts unless user explicitly asks.
- Before any commit operation, verify staged files do not include secrets/runtime outputs and abort if they do.

## Run Directory Layout
`runs/YYYY-MM-DD/<slug>/run_<HH-MM-SSam>/runtime.db` -- 4 levels deep under `runs/`.
Path math that assumes fewer levels will silently read the wrong database.

